The Five Cities form a co-dependent trade and legal network, not a military alliance.
Each city fills one role in a chain: origin claim, overland custody, dispute adjudication, hazard screening, ocean transfer.
Removing any city strains the others predictably.

Midgaard: inland legitimacy engine. Registries, charters, sealed-warrant governance, codified arbitration.
Kiess: legal-memory city on Evermeet's ruins along Roc Road. Anti-secrecy charter. Anti-Conclave stance.
Kowloon: northern throughput node. Moves and counts goods. Neon Covenant governance is the most stable of the five.
Rakuen (Saltglass): southern hazard screening. Three times petitioned Midgaard for annexation, three times refused.
Mafdet: maritime authority at Saltglass Reach terminus. Dual-attestation protocol converts inland cargo to shipborne contract cargo.

Midgaard and Kowloon share the deepest tension: both participated in the Conclave's condemned-debtor transfer system.
Both have Reckoning factions seeking exposure and Continuity factions seeking burial.
Kiess was founded explicitly to repudiate Midgaard's sealed-warrant governance.
Rakuen's repeated annexation requests reshaped intercity law across all five cities.
